transcript.text: Hello, welcome to the on Print shop.
In today's video, we will introduce you to the custom form builder.
This feature allows you to create customized forms to collect data from your customers as per the business requirement.
To get started, in the admin panel, navigate to the Store configuration menu and you can locate the Manage forms.
The previous Manage Form Fields user interface has been enhanced to enable you to create new custom forms via the Add button and the form fields via the Manage Form Fields button.
To create a new form, you first need to create the fields and then assign them to the form.
Here we have taken an example of Product Interest survey form.
As you can see, relevant form fields are already created and assigned to the form.
For creating fields for custom forms, we have introduced the new form field type Custom Form.
Now for the new form, select the store where the form should be displayed.
Give a title such as Product, Interest, Survey form.
Choose the layout of the form to display form fields either in one column or in two columns.
Choose to notify admin or customer and at the end enable the status of the form as active.
Now it is time to assign the custom form fields.
So let's select these fields and if you want you can change the sequence of the fields by simply dragging and dropping as per your need.
Once you are done, click on Save and Back button to display the created form on the website.
You need to add a block to the CMS page.
As you can see, we have created one CMS page named Product Interest Survey.
To display the form, you need to add the custom form block in the page content section along with the form unique ID separated with a pipe.
Save the details to see how this form will appear on the website.
Click on the preview icon available on the list page.
And that's it.
This is how you can create forms tailored to your requirements.
Additionally, every time any of your customers or website visitors submit the form, you can simply check the stats from the View form submissions icon against the respective forms created.
Thank you for watching this tutorial, We hope you found it helpful.
If you have any questions, feel free to reach out to our support team.
